<br>
1. All books must be by published authors, not web authors (ie: you can't use a story that someone is writing on GLO)<br>
2. Author's names must be put in parenthesis after book titles<br>
3. If you haven't read a book then DO NOT rate it! Let someone who has read the book rate it. I am sick of seeing 'I haven't read it' or even worse, &quot;Never heard of it&quot;. Those posts will be edited out along with the rating for the book listed in said post in the following post.<br>
4. In order to keep things under control, please do not start any topics in here. If you have an idea, feel free to post it in the topic I will be stickying and I will consider it.<br>
5. Please do not just post something like &quot;umm...I don't know.&quot; Those types of posts serve absolutely no purpose, and do not further the game. As such, these posts will also be deleted.<br>
<br>
These are all the rules for now, but if I think of more, I will add them. Please read these and check back every so often.<br>
<br>
